a blender does suggest a certain...

01:07:40.280 --> 01:07:43.750
1950s reference
to sexual politics, but...

01:07:43.880 --> 01:07:48.271
I swear, it never entered
my consciousness at the time.

01:07:48.400 --> 01:07:51.915
- I believe you.
- You do?

01:07:53.840 --> 01:07:56.115
Would you tell Annie
that for me, Dad?

01:07:56.240 --> 01:07:59.232
This was where I was gonna
lower the boom.

01:07:59.360 --> 01:08:03.114
But instead, I looked into his
weepy eyes and found my self saying--

01:08:03.240 --> 01:08:07.552
- Sure, I'll tell her.
- Oh, good!

01:08:07.680 --> 01:08:11.070
'Cause I know whatever you say
she'll believe.

01:08:11.200 --> 01:08:13.111
Not only was I not getting rid
of the kid...

01:08:13.240 --> 01:08:16.118
I now found myself
talking him into staying.

01:08:16.240 --> 01:08:19.630
You know, Bryan,
Annie's a very passionate person.

01:08:19.760 --> 01:08:23.469
And passionate people tend
to overreact at time.

01:08:23.600 --> 01:08:28.037
Annie comes from a long line
of major overreactors.

01:08:28.160 --> 01:08:31.277
Me. I can definitely lose it.

01:08:31.399 --> 01:08:33.834
My mother. A nut.

01:08:33.960 --> 01:08:37.270
My grandfather.
Stories about him were legendary.

01:08:39.080 --> 01:08:42.072
The good news, however,
is that this overreacting...

01:08:42.200 --> 01:08:45.158
tends to get proportionately less
by generation.

01:08:45.279 --> 01:08:48.670
So, your kids could be normal.

01:08:51.960 --> 01:08:54.599
As if that wasn't enough,
I went on.

01:08:54.720 --> 01:08:58.508
But on the upside,
with this passion...

01:08:58.640 --> 01:09:01.393
comes great spirit
and individuality...

01:09:01.520 --> 01:09:05.559
which is probably
one of the reasons you love Annie.

01:09:05.680 --> 01:09:08.240
That's what
I love most about her.

01:09:08.359 --> 01:09:11.158
