01:29:02.120 --> 01:29:06.716
It was unbelievable.
I had never seen a line form so fast.

01:29:06.840 --> 01:29:10.310
It was as if they knew
what the food was costing me.

01:29:12.880 --> 01:29:15.030
Finally,
I made it into the tent.

01:29:21.120 --> 01:29:23.236
I was ready to relax and taste
the food I'd been hearing about...

01:29:23.360 --> 01:29:25.032
for the past five months, when--

01:29:25.160 --> 01:29:29.233
Dad! Dad! There's some cops out front,
and they want to talk to you!

01:29:29.360 --> 01:29:32.033
- Cops?
- I've heard. We'll handle dis togather.

01:29:32.160 --> 01:29:34.037
I got George. Ve're on our vay.

01:29:34.160 --> 01:29:36.230
Come on, George.
Pick it up. Pick it up.

01:29:38.920 --> 01:29:40.672
One-Adam-seventy, roger.
Standby.

01:29:40.800 --> 01:29:43.189
Let me handle this, George.
Give me your wallet.

01:29:43.320 --> 01:29:45.117
Stop!

01:29:45.240 --> 01:29:48.994
- Adam-30, disregard.
- What is this?

01:29:49.120 --> 01:29:53.113
- See, Cameron? I told ya.
- Wow!

01:29:53.240 --> 01:29:55.629
Just try to smile. That's all.

01:29:55.760 --> 01:29:57.876
- This your house?
- Me?

01:29:58.000 --> 01:30:01.549
Yeah, you. In the blue tux.

01:30:01.680 --> 01:30:06.515
- Yes. Yes, it is.
- Do you have a permit for parking
200 cars in this street?

01:30:06.640 --> 01:30:11.839
Vell, the-- the problem is, Officer,
dat we are supposed to haf
four parking attandants.

01:30:11.960 --> 01:30:14.315
- Uh, but two got de flu.
- Well, you better get...

01:30:14.440 --> 01:30:17.273
all these cars off this street
before the fire marshall gets here.

01:30:17.400 --> 01:30:19.436
Fine, fine. Any sugjoostions
what we do with them?

01:30:19.560 --> 01:30:22.472
I don't care what you do with them.
Just have them off this street
within the next 30 minutes.

01:30:22.600 --> 01:30:25.876
Vill do, sir. Ve'll take care of it.
You're not to worry, okay?

01:30:26.000 --> 01:30:28.639
- Franck? Where are you? The cake--
- Uh, uh, George. They need me inside.

01:30:28.760 --> 01:30:31.320
Uh, the big moment.
The keck is being wheeled out!

01:30:31.440 --> 01:30:35.149
- I-- I-- I'll handle this.
- I'm on my vay!

01:30:35.280 --> 01:30:37.840
Where're we gonna get
a couple extra drivers?

01:30:44.760 --> 01:30:48.799
Hey, baby, I'm your man
Turn around, you'll see

01:30:48.920 --> 01:30:51.070
I may not stand tall
and I don't talk neat

01:30:51.200 --> 01:30:54.112
But I'm gonna
win your love for me

01:30:57.440 --> 01:30:59.829
Yes!

01:30:59.960 --> 01:31:04.158
Watch out, baby, here comes your man
Lookin' cool to me

01:31:04.840 --> 01:31:06.717
Whoa!

01:31:12.080 --> 01:31:14.116
By the way,
great wedding, Mr Banks.

01:31:14.240 --> 01:31:16.879
And don't worry!
I didn't eat anything!

01:31:17.000 --> 01:31:21.676
- That makes two of us.
- I got sunshine

01:31:21.800 --> 01:31:24.553
On a cloudy day

01:31:24.680 --> 01:31:27.592
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

01:31:27.720 --> 01:31:30.917
When it's cold outside

01:31:31.040 --> 01:31:34.476
I've got the month of May

01:31:36.960 --> 01:31:41.351
I guess you'll say

01:31:41.480 --> 01:31:45.678
What can make me feel this way

01:31:45.800 --> 01:31:49.315
- It's my girl
- My girl, my girl

01:31:49.440 --> 01:31:52.238
I will feel aglow

01:31:52.360 --> 01:31:57.593
Just thinkin' of you

01:31:57.720 --> 01:32:01.315
And the way you look

01:32:01.440 --> 01:32:03.556
Tonight

01:32:09.200 --> 01:32:14.399
- I know.
- Oh, but you're lovely

01:32:14.520 --> 01:32:18.479
With your smile so warm

01:32:18.600 --> 01:32:22.832
And your cheeks so soft

01:32:22.960 --> 01:32:26.191
There is nothing for me

01:32:26.320 --> 01:32:30.029
But to love you

01:32:31.200 --> 01:32:34.670
Just the way you look

01:32:34.800 --> 01:32:36.836
Tonight

01:32:43.880 --> 01:32:47.759
Just the way you look

01:32:50.160 --> 01:32:51.752
- Tonight
- Well, I had to admit...

01:32:51.880 --> 01:32:54.678
the wedding appeared to be
a complete success.

01:32:54.800 --> 01:32:57.712
Now, all I needed to make me happy
was a dance with the bride.

01:32:57.840 --> 01:33:01.276
- It's time.
- Ladies and gentlemen...

01:33:01.400 --> 01:33:05.916
in just a few moments,
Mrs Annie Banks-MacKenzie will be
tossing her bouquet in the foyer.

01:33:06.040 --> 01:33:08.235
- And then she's off to Hawaii.
- Let's go in there. Oh, sorry.

01:33:08.360 --> 01:33:11.432
- Excuse me. Thank you.
- This I was not going to miss.

01:33:11.560 --> 01:33:13.994
- Comin' through.
- The mob was headed
through the living room...

01:33:14.120 --> 01:33:17.396
- so I decided to take a shortcut.
- Sorry.

01:33:17.520 --> 01:33:19.272
- Excuse me. Thank you.
- Great wedding, George!

01:33:19.400 --> 01:33:21.675
- Had a lovely time.
- Thanks. Excuse me.
- Great party, George.

01:33:21.800 --> 01:33:23.995
Hurry up!

01:33:28.240 --> 01:33:30.071
Whoa! Ay-yi-yi-yi!

01:33:31.600 --> 01:33:33.716
Whoo!

01:33:45.120 --> 01:33:47.395
- Where's my dad?
- I-- I-- I don't know.

01:33:47.520 --> 01:33:52.116
- I haven't seen him.
- Watch it. Behind you.

01:33:52.240 --> 01:33:54.196
Excuse me.

01:33:56.840 --> 01:34:00.150
- Should I throw it?
- Yeah! Yes!

01:34:04.160 --> 01:34:05.832
He missed it.

01:34:09.160 --> 01:34:11.390
- Bye-bye!
- Let us through. Let us--

01:34:16.240 --> 01:34:18.959
Bye!

01:34:19.080 --> 01:34:21.036
Goodbye, Charlie!

01:34:21.160 --> 01:34:23.037
Bye, Bryan!

01:34:25.080 --> 01:34:26.479
- Bye!
- Bye!
- Thanks.

01:34:26.600 --> 01:34:29.239
- Bye!
- Have fun!

01:34:33.120 --> 01:34:36.556
She was gone.
My Annie was gone...

01:34:36.680 --> 01:34:39.797
and I was too late
to say goodbye.

01:34:59.240 --> 01:35:00.559
When the last guest was gone...

01:35:00.680 --> 01:35:03.513
and the last glass of champagne
had been drunk...

01:35:03.640 --> 01:35:05.870
we surveyed the damage.

01:35:15.480 --> 01:35:18.278
It's funny how empty a house
can suddenly get, isn't it?

01:35:18.400 --> 01:35:22.996
Yeah. I'm sorry you didn't get a chance
to say goodbye to her, George.

01:35:23.120 --> 01:35:26.112
Oh, that's all right.

01:35:26.240 --> 01:35:29.152
But, you know, I think she's going
to be really happy.

01:35:29.280 --> 01:35:32.955
Oh, yeah. Sure.

01:35:43.880 --> 01:35:46.599
- Hello?
- Dad!

01:35:46.720 --> 01:35:49.393
Hi! Where are you?

01:35:49.520 --> 01:35:51.317
At the airport.
Our plane's about to take off...

01:35:51.440 --> 01:35:53.795
but I couldn't leave
without saying goodbye.

01:35:53.920 --> 01:35:56.832
Thank Mom for everything, okay?

01:35:56.960 --> 01:35:59.315
And Dad...

01:35:59.440 --> 01:36:01.351
I love you.

01:36:01.480 --> 01:36:04.631
I love you very much.

01:36:04.760 --> 01:36:06.637
I love you too, sweetheart.

01:36:06.760 --> 01:36:10.753
Thanks for calling.
And have a great honeymoon.

01:36:10.880 --> 01:36:14.998
Thanks. I will. Bye.

01:36:15.720 --> 01:36:19.030
Someday

01:36:19.160 --> 01:36:23.517
When I'm awfully low

01:36:23.640 --> 01:36:27.269
- When the world is cold
- That was Annie.

01:36:27.400 --> 01:36:30.472
- Oh.
- I will feel aglow

01:36:30.600 --> 01:36:35.674
Just thinkin' of you

01:36:35.800 --> 01:36:39.509
And the way you look

01:36:39.640 --> 01:36:41.596
Tonight

01:36:48.000 --> 01:36:52.471
Oh, but you're lovely

01:36:52.600 --> 01:36:56.673
With your smile so warm

01:36:56.800 --> 01:37:00.793
And your cheeks so soft

01:37:00.920 --> 01:37:04.390
There is nothin' for me

